Welcome to the W3C Exploration Interest Group (IG).

We are delighted to have you join us. Our mission is to provide W3C Members with a forum to explore and discuss emerging web-related technology trends and consider how the community could collaborate to shape those trends for the benefit of web users.

This is a short introduction email to provide useful links about the group.
You will find a lot of information about the Exploration IG linked from 
  https://www.w3.org/groups/ig/exploration/

In particular, the following page tells you where the Exploration IG works, including repositories
  https://www.w3.org/groups/ig/exploration/tools/
  
For meetings, check the group calendar at
  https://www.w3.org/groups/ig/exploration/calendar/

The group primarily conducts its work on GitHub
  https://github.com/w3c/exploration-ig/

If you have not already done so, please link your GitHub account to your W3C account using
  https://www.w3.org/users/myprofile/connectedaccounts/

All participants in the Exploration IG are expected to behave in accordance with the W3C Code of Conduct
  https://www.w3.org/policies/code-of-conduct/

If you have any questions or concerns, you can reach the group chairs and team contact (in Cc of this message) directly. Contact information is also available on
  https://www.w3.org/groups/ig/exploration/participants/

